![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a05bf093-b4f7-47b7-93f6-c860d15dc841/20240410_005804.jpg?format=original)

The grand spectacle of WrestleMania continues to captivate audiences around the world, with the latest edition, WrestleMania 40, breaking records and leaving a lasting impression on fans. According to NBCU, WrestleMania 40 amassed an impressive 1.3 billion live minutes of account watch time on the streaming platform Peacock.

Wrestlenomics, a platform dedicated to analyzing the business side of professional wrestling, provided further insight into the viewership numbers for WrestleMania 40. By utilizing the combined run time of 469 minutes for the event, Wrestlenomics estimated that an average of 2.7 million to 2.9 million Peacock accounts (not to be confused with individual viewers) tuned in to watch the festivities unfold.

These figures highlight the significant impact of WrestleMania on the streaming landscape and reaffirm its status as a must-see event for wrestling enthusiasts worldwide. The transition to streaming platforms like Peacock has enabled WWE to reach a broader audience and adapt to changing viewing habits in the digital age.

WrestleMania 40 featured a star-studded lineup of matches, including high-stakes championship clashes, epic showdowns between iconic rivals, and show-stopping moments that left fans on the edge of their seats. From the electrifying atmosphere of the stadium to the comfort of living rooms around the globe, viewers experienced the thrill of WrestleMania like never before.

As WWE continues to innovate and evolve its programming, WrestleMania remains the crown jewel of the wrestling calendar, captivating audiences with its blend of athleticism, drama, and spectacle. With record-breaking viewership numbers and a legacy that spans decades, WrestleMania 40 has once again proven why it holds a special place in the hearts of wrestling fans everywhere.